All members of the Heroku application
can create a new release by pushing code
to Heroku and triggering a deployment.
Other developers need to fork the project
Github repository and send in pull requests
added git and github workflow image
Github provides forking and pull requests
on top of the standard Git commands.
You fork a project when you wish to
Pull requests let the project team know
you have changes you want to share.
